The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, April 15: Jet Airways is planning a makeover. The company will soon have a new logo, its fleet of planes could sport a new colour and the cabin crew will be sporting a new uniform. Travellers, too, will be treated to new seats. Sources said the company has decided on a new look because of the competition from Kingfisher Airlines. Jet has no plans to use the Air Sahara brand for six months.

 New Delhi, April 15: itc Ltd plans to invest about Rs 15,000 crore in the next five to seven years in hotels, agri-business and fmcg as it seeks to transform its image into a diversified corporate conglomerate. The company plans to rev up its social farm forestry projects in Andhra Pradesh and Karnataka, which will involve 12 lakh farmers by 2012-14, up from three lakh now.

 Bangalore, April 15: Finance minister P. Chidambaram has said the immediate goal of the government is to moderate inflation to about 5 per cent or so and asserted that it was taking every step in this regard.

 New Delhi, April 15: Indias export growth rate has declined to a single digit from about 24 per cent in April-November 2006 due to the appreciation in rupee, Federation of Indian Exporters Organisation president Ganesh K. Gupta said.

 Mumbai, April 15: Indian Oil Corporation eyes a Rs 1,000-crore turnover from its non-fuel operations (lpg centres) in the next three to five years compared with Rs 180 crore in fiscal 2007.




